ata-id="5026" src="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-10-13-at-11.27.49-2-1024x725.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-5026" srcset="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-10-13-at-11.27.49-2-1024x725.jpeg 1024w, https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-10-13-at-11.27.49-2-980x693.jpeg 980w, https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-10-13-at-11.27.49-2-480x340.jpeg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="725" data-id="5020" src="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-10-13-at-11.27.49-1024x725.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-5020" srcset="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-10-13-at-11.27.49-1024x725.jpeg 1024w, https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-10-13-at-11.27.49-980x694.jpeg 980w, https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-10-13-at-11.27.49-480x340.jpeg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="724" data-id="5035" src="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-10-13-at-11.27.50-1024x724.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-5035" srcset="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-10-13-at-11.27.50-980x693.jpeg 980w, https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-10-13-at-11.27.50-480x339.jpeg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></figure>\n</figure>\n<p>The post <a href="https://ilrigsa.org.za/ilrig-at-the-2nd-trajects-global-academy/">ILRIG at the 2nd TRAJECTS Global Academy</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ilrigsa.org.za">ILRIG</a>.</p>\n	2025-10-13 09:33:06+00	f	0880ff16-e89c-4795-9d58-2e1f8e8615cd	\N	<p>Last week, ILRIG participated in the 2nd TRAJECTS Global Academy, held in Cape Town from 610 October 2025, under the theme Re-imagining Climate Change Technocratic Responses: Pathways Towards Regenerative Futures. The Academy brought together early-career practitioners, researchers, and activists from across South Africa, Colombia, and beyond for a week of dialogue, exchange, and collective unlearning. [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a href="https://ilrigsa.org.za/ilrig-at-the-2nd-trajects-global-academy/">ILRIG at the 2nd TRAJECTS Global Academy</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ilrigsa.org.za">ILRIG</a>.</p>\n
ca693e45-d880-46ca-95de-a3896a06e99a	2025-10-18 13:00:10.676589+00	2025-10-18 13:00:10.682776+00	\N	LGBTQI++ Feminist School 2025	en-ZA	https://ilrigsa.org.za/lgbtqi-feminist-school-2025/	\n<p>From <strong>2226 September 2025</strong>, ILRIG hosted the <strong>FeministQueer School</strong> in Johannesburg  a budy week of learning, discussion and activism aimed at <strong>bridging the gap between womxns and LGBTQI++ struggles</strong>. Bringing together activists, organisers and change-makers from across South Africa, the school created a space to explore how feminism and queer liberation intersect in the fight against rising right-wing oppression, neoliberalism, patriarchy and capitalism.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Through workshops, film screenings, debates and creative sessions, participants unpacked topics ranging from the history of feminist thought and the rise of anti-gender ideology, to the lived realities of queer and womxn workers under todays global crises. Sessions on <strong>radical feminism, resistance art, decolonial theory, and solidarity across struggles</strong> helped deepen connections between movements that are too often separated by propaganda.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The schools spirit was one of <strong>collective care and creative resistance</strong>  featuring writing workshops, a Pride march organised by participants, and sessions led by comrades from Queers for Palestine and African Workers Forum. These moments reminded everyone that liberation must be both political and joyful, rooted in mutual aid, and committed to transforming the world we live in.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>ILRIG thanks all participants, facilitators and partner movements who made the 2025 FeministQueer School a success. Together, we continue to imagine and build inclusive, anti-capitalist futures where all genders are recognised and valued.<br><br>Keep a look out for further events ILRIG plans to do in this field. If you have ideas for collaboration or any additions to this area of popular education &#8211; please get in touch with us. Let&#8217;s work together! Contact &#105;&#108;&#114;i&#103;sa&#64;g&#109;&#97;&#105;l.c&#111;&#109; </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s a short creative compilation video intro </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe loading="lazy" title="ILRIG LGBTQI++ and Feminist  school 2025" width="1080" height="608" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/fUgmej6EG7Y?feature=oembed"  allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><br><br>Also, some of our favourite photos</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-2 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex">\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" data-id="4985" src="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-09-22-at-21.00.26-1-1024x576.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-4985" srcset="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-09-22-at-21.00.26-1-980x551.jpeg 980w, https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-09-22-at-21.00.26-1-480x270.jpeg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="724" data-id="4986" src="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-09-22-at-21.00.27-2-1024x724.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-4986" srcset="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-09-22-at-21.00.27-2-980x693.jpeg 980w, https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-c