ared first on <a href="https://ilrigsa.org.za">ILRIG</a>.</p>\n	2025-10-07 09:23:08+00	f	0880ff16-e89c-4795-9d58-2e1f8e8615cd	\N	<p>From 2226 September 2025, ILRIG hosted the FeministQueer School in Johannesburg  a budy week of learning, discussion and activism aimed at bridging the gap between womxns and LGBTQI++ struggles. Bringing together activists, organisers and change-makers from across South Africa, the school created a space to explore how feminism and queer liberation intersect in the [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a href="https://ilrigsa.org.za/lgbtqi-feminist-school-2025/">LGBTQI++ Feminist School 2025</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ilrigsa.org.za">ILRIG</a>.</p>\n
a36e820e-4651-45e7-ae1b-304ce2533641	2025-10-18 13:00:10.734098+00	2025-10-18 13:00:10.735452+00	\N	Climate Injustice: Climate Change is a Working-Class Issue	en-ZA	https://ilrigsa.org.za/climate-injustice-climate-change-is-a-working-class-issue-2/	\n<p><strong>Date 2 may</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Time 12 &#8211; 3pm<br>Venue: Community House, 41 Saltriver road, Saltriver.&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Please&nbsp;</strong><strong>RSVP:</strong><a>&#105;&#108;&#114;igsa&#64;&#103;&#109;a&#105;&#108;.c&#111;&#109;</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><br>The event is also available online</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Join online:</strong><a href="https://us02web.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_EVwcm8WASQGkPLHAm3henQ" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Register here</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>About the book:</strong><br>ILRIGs&nbsp;<em>Climate Injustice</em>&nbsp;pamphlet unpacks how climate change is not just an environmental crisisits a political and economic issue rooted in deep global inequality.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This pamphlet offers accessible analysis, local and global context, and a clear call to action. As floods, fires, and food and water insecurity intensify, the need for organised resistance has never been more urgent.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We dont just need climate actionwe need&nbsp;<strong>system change, not climate change</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Speakers</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Lara French</strong>&nbsp; Researcher and activist committed to climate justice and the just transition. She authored this pamphlet to help communities understand the impact of climate change and why it must be part of our broader activism.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Mpumi Mhlalisi</strong>&nbsp; An environmental and social justice activist, Mpuni served on the Western Cape Provincial Coordinating Committee of the Environmental Justice Networking Forum and worked with GenderCC on climate resilience. Mpumi co-authored&nbsp;<em>Trouble in the Air</em>&nbsp;(edited by Patrick Bond) and currently serves on the South African and Western Cape Water Caucus committees.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-5 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex">\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="770" data-id="4920" src="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/20250502_125539-1024x770.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-4920" srcset="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/20250502_125539-980x737.jpg 980w, https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/20250502_125539-480x361.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="718" data-id="4919" src="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/20250502_125931-1-1024x718.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-4919" srcset="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/20250502_125931-1-980x688.jpg 980w, https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/20250502_125931-1-480x337.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="768" data-id="4921" src="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/20250502_132448-1024x768.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-4921" srcset="https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/20250502_132448-980x735.jpg 980w, https://ilrigsa.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/20250502_132448-480x360.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></figure>\n</figure>\n<p>The post <