lass="wpb_wrapper"></div></div></div><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-4"><div class="vc_column-inner"><div class="wpb_wrapper"></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner"><div class="wpb_wrapper"></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner"><div class="wpb_wrapper"></div></div></div></div>\n</div><p>The post <a href="https://www.opensecrets.org.za/who-owns-south-africa-the-dan-corder-show/">Who Owns South Africa? | The Dan Corder Show</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.opensecrets.org.za">Open Secrets</a>.</p>\n	2025-10-07 16:06:22+00	f	0744ad9c-d1c8-45d1-863d-0ccd1723ada7	\N	<p>Michael Marchant, Head of Investigations at Open Secrets was a guest on The Dan Corder Show on eNCA explaining Open Secrets' research into the billionaires and big businesses that own much of South Africa's industries.</p>\n<p>The post <a href="https://www.opensecrets.org.za/who-owns-south-africa-the-dan-corder-show/">Who Owns South Africa? | The Dan Corder Show</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.opensecrets.org.za">Open Secrets</a>.</p>\n
67a24026-8b21-4c0f-82cd-91725dc41713	2025-10-18 13:01:15.536497+00	2025-10-18 13:01:15.542481+00	\N	Who Owns South Africa report points to commodification of healthcare in private sector | Daily Maverick	en-GB	https://www.opensecrets.org.za/who-owns-south-africa-report-points-to-commodification-of-healthcare-in-private-sector-daily-maverick/	<div class="wpb-content-wrapper"><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid vc_custom_1754475253921"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner vc_custom_1753861151816"><div class="wpb_wrapper"><h1 style="font-size: 36px;color: #000000;line-height: 110%;text-align: left;font-family:Open Sans;font-weight:700;font-style:normal" class="vc_custom_heading vc_do_custom_heading vc_custom_1753861170720" >&#8216;Who Owns South Africa report points to commodification of healthcare in private sector | Daily Maverick</h1></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid vc_custom_1753862027812"><div class="n-post-column wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-8"><div class="vc_column-inner vc_custom_1754995215906"><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_inner vc_row-fluid vc_custom_1754475179817 vc_row-o-content-bottom vc_row-flex"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-8"><div class="vc_column-inner vc_custom_1754474794234"><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div class="category-chips"><a href='https://www.opensecrets.org.za/category/news/' class='category-chip'>News</a> <a href='https://www.opensecrets.org.za/category/news/print-media-online/' class='category-chip'>Print Media Online</a> <a href='https://www.opensecrets.org.za/category/theme/state-capture-profiteers/' class='category-chip'>State Capture Profiteers</a> <a href='https://www.opensecrets.org.za/category/theme/state-capture-profiteers/who-owns-south-africa/' class='category-chip'>Who Owns South Africa?</a> </div></div></div></div><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-4"><div class="vc_column-inner vc_custom_1754475316700"><div class="wpb_wrapper"></div></div></div></div>\n\t<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >\n\t\t<div class="wpb_wrapper">\n\t\t\t<p>A report by the nonprofit Open Secrets has condemned the financialisation of healthcare in South Africa, with researchers arguing that the private healthcare sector is being used for profit-taking by a small group of powerful actors at the expense of affordability and access for patients.</p>\n\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div id="post-template-featured-image" class="wpb_single_image wpb_content_element vc_align_left  vc_custom_1753870857081">\n\t\t\n\t\t<figure class="wpb_wrapper vc_figure">\n\t\t\t<div class="vc_single_image-wrapper vc_box_rounded  vc_box_border_grey"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1606" height="1069" src="https://www.opensecrets.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Luvano-Fatima.webp" class="vc_single_image-img attachment-full" alt="" title="Luvano Fatima" srcset="https://www.opensecrets.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Luvano-Fatima.webp 1606w, https://www.opensecrets.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Luvano-Fatima-768x511.webp 768w, https://www.opensecrets.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Luvano-Fatima-1536x1022.webp 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 1606px) 100vw, 1606px"  data-dt-location="https://www.opensecrets.org.za/who-owns-south-africa-report-points-to-commodification-of-healthcare-in-private-sector-daily-maverick/luvano-fatima/" /></div>\n\t\t</figure>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element  vc_custom_1759415828585 authors-box-round" >\n\t\t<div class="wpb_wrapper">\n\t\t\tOctober 6, 2025\n\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >\n\t\t<div class="wpb_wrapper">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Originally published in <a href="https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/article/2025-10-02-report-points-to-commodification-of-healthcare-in-sasprivate-sector/">Daily Maverick</a> </strong></p>\n<p><strong>By <a title="Tamsin Metelerkamp" href="https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/author/tamsin-metelerkamp/" target="_self">Tamsin Metelerkamp </a></strong></p>\n<p>Released on Tuesday, 30 September, the report spotlights the commodification of healthcare in South Africa, with researchers arguing that private health services are being used for profit by a small group of powerful local and international financial actors who see healthcare as little more than a collection of assets to trade.</p>\n<p>There are over nine million people covered by medical aid in South Africa, with around 4.8 million (52%) covered by open schemes. Discovery, Bonitas and Momentum, the three largest medical aid schemes cover over four million of these, the report states.</p>\n<p>It comes at a key moment in the debate over South Africas ailing health system, as the battle over the implementation of the controversial National Health Insurance (NHI) Act  signed into law last year  manoeuvres through the countrys courts&#8230;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n<style type="text/css" data-type="the7_shortcodes-inline-css">#default-btn-464abb40b1d695b3f079571e92150c54.ico-right-side > i {\n  margin-right: 0px;\n  margin-left: 8px;\n}\n#default-btn-464abb40b1d695b3f079571e92150c54 > i {\n  margin-right: 8px;\n}\n</style><div class="btn-align-center"><a href="https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/article/2025-10-02-report-points-to-commodification-of-healthcare-in-sasprivate-sector/?dm_source=dm_block_grid&amp;dm_medium=card_link&amp;dm_campaign=main" class="default-btn-shortcode dt-btn dt-btn-m link-hover-off " target="_blank" id="default-btn-464abb40b1d695b3f079571e92150c54" title="Read more" rel="noopener"><span>Read more</span></a></div><div class="vc_empty_space"   style="height: 32px"><span class="vc_empty_space_inner"></span></div><div class='root-data-givewp-embed' data-form-locale='en_GB' data-form-url='https://www.opensecrets.org.za/?post_type=give_forms&#038;p=12186' data-form-view-url='https://www.opensecret