sm-8"><div class="vc_column-inner"><div class="wpb_wrapper"></div></div></div><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-4"><div class="vc_column-inner"><div class="wpb_wrapper"></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner"><div class="wpb_wrapper"></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner"><div class="wpb_wrapper"></div></div></div></div>\n</div><p>The post <a href="https://www.opensecrets.org.za/investigation-who-owns-south-africa-private-healthcare-medical-aid-schemes-and-private-hospitals/">INVESTIGATION | Who Owns South Africa? &#8211; Private Healthcare: Medical Aid Schemes and Private Hospitals</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.opensecrets.org.za">Open Secrets</a>.</p>\n	2025-09-30 04:55:12+00	f	0744ad9c-d1c8-45d1-863d-0ccd1723ada7	\N	<p>South Africas healthcare sector is marred by deep rooted inequalities, with millions relying on an overly strained and under resourced public healthcare system. In this instalment of Who Owns South Africa, Open Secrets turns the spotlight on to the role of private players in the health care system and shows how the concentration of private power shapes the sector. </p>\n<p>The post <a href="https://www.opensecrets.org.za/investigation-who-owns-south-africa-private-healthcare-medical-aid-schemes-and-private-hospitals/">INVESTIGATION | Who Owns South Africa? &#8211; Private Healthcare: Medical Aid Schemes and Private Hospitals</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.opensecrets.org.za">Open Secrets</a>.</p>\n
