213d137f-da2c-48a0-88c9-0b034f033318	2025-10-18 13:01:17.914847+00	2025-10-18 13:01:17.91647+00	\N	The South Durban Community Environmental Alliance Presents the National Oil and Gas Conference Where Unity Will Shape Tomorrows Sustainable Future.	en-US	https://groundwork.org.za/the-south-durban-community-environmental-alliance-presents-the-national-oil-and-gas-conference-were-unity-will-shape-tomorrows-sustainable-future/	<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>PRESS STATEMENT</strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>South Durban Community Environmental Alliance (SDCEA)</strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Date: 31 August 2025</strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong></strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>The South Durban Community Environmental Alliance Presents the National Oil and Gas Conference </strong><strong>Were Unity Will Shape Tomorrows Sustainable Future.</strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;">The South Durban Community Environmental Alliance (SDCEA) is proud to announce the upcoming National Oil and Gas Conference, taking place on the 3<sup>rd</sup> and 4<sup>th</sup> of September 2025 at the Blue Waters Hotel in Durban, located in KwaZulu-Natal. This important event will bring together stakeholders from across South Africa such as environmental and social justice organizations, fisherfolk, coastal communities, researchers, conservationists and media to engage in open, informed, and impactful dialogues on the impacts of oil and gas developments. Following the theme <strong>Protecting Our Land and Oceans, Securing Our Future,</strong> this conference will give the attendees a national platform to explore the impacts of oil and gas developments, challenges that affect the various communities, and the available options towards a sustainable future for South Africa.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Why This Conference Matters</strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;">Oil and Gas developments in South Africa are at the forefront of critical debates in the environmental and social justice sector. This conference will unpack the impacts and issues that communities have faced and create collaborative solutions through keynote presentations, panel discussions, breakaway sessions, and stakeholder dialogues.</p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Key Highlights:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Distinguished speakers from environmental and social justice organizations.</li>\n<li>Community perspectives highlighting the voices and experiences of those directly impacted by oil and gas developments.</li>\n<li>Policy and regulatory insights to help communities understand the legal side of these developments.</li>\n<li>Networking opportunities to connect those affected, with organizations that have the ability to change this and the media that can expose these impacts.</li>\n</ul>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong></strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;">Speakers will include representatives from leading environmental and social justice organizations, researchers, community leaders, legal experts, and fisherfolk organizations, who will share powerful testimonies and evidence on the pressing need to stop oil and gas developments.</p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong></strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>A Call to the Media</strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;">Members of the press are invited to attend and cover this important event, which promises to tackle the issues of oil and gas developments through thought-provoking discussions. SDCEA recognizes the vital role that journalists play in shaping public awareness and holding the wrong accountable. Therefore, please join us and gain firsthand access to insights shared, community stories, and exclusive interview opportunities with key stakeholders driving the movement against fossil fuel expansion.</p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Event Details:</strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;">Dates: 3 and 4 September 2025</p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;">Venue: Blue Waters Hotel</p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;">Location: Durban, KwaZulu-Natal</p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;">Time: 08:00am-17:00pm</p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;">Theme: Protecting our land and oceans, securing our future.</p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><em>Join us at the National Oil and Gas Conference, </em><em>at a time when the fight for climate and ocean justice has never been more urgent and </em><em>where knowledge will meet action.</em></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong></strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>For more information, please contact:</strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>South Durban Community Environmental Alliance (SDCEA)</strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Tel: [</strong><strong>068 753 5250</strong><strong>]</strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Email: Nom</strong><strong>fundo [</strong><strong>n&#111;mf&#117;n&#100;&#111;&#64;&#115;&#100;c&#101;&#97;n&#103;&#111;&#46;c&#111;&#46;&#122;&#97;]</strong></p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Website: [https://sdcea.co.za/]</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a href="https://groundwork.org.za/the-south-durban-community-environmental-alliance-presents-the-national-oil-and-gas-conference-were-unity-will-shape-tomorrows-sustainable-future/">The South Durban Community Environmental Alliance Presents the National Oil and Gas Conference Where Unity Will Shape Tomorrows Sustainable Future.</a> appeared first on <a href="https://groundwork.org.za">groundWork</a>.</p>\n	2025-09-02 08:07:47+00	f	0fcc0a30-d0f9-48bd-be80-c75c1e8dbaf1	\N	<p>PRESS STATEMENT South Durban Community Environmental Alliance (SDCEA) Date: 31 August 2025  The South Durban Community Environmental Alliance Presents the National Oil and Gas Conference Were Unity Will Shape Tomorrows Sustainable Future. The South Durban Community Environmental Alliance (SDCEA) is proud to announce the upcoming National Oil and Gas Conference, taking place on the [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a href="https://groundwork.org.za/the-south-durban-community-environmental-alliance-presents-the-national-oil-and-gas-conference-were-unity-will-shape-tomorrows-sustainable-future/">The South Durban Community Environmental Alliance Presents the National Oil and Gas Conference Where Unity Will Shape Tomorrows Sustainable Future.</a> appeared first on <a href="https://groundwork.org.za">groundWork</a>.</p>\n
